      <article class="span6 main">
       <p>
        The University of Chicagoâs Comprehensive Emergency Management Program outlines strategies to protect the life safety of University students, faculty, and staff, and to preserve University property and assets in the event of an emergency. The Emergency Management website is a resource the University community can use to receive information on how to prepare for emergencies and how to protect themselves from the effects of an emergency.
       </p>
       <p>
        <img alt="Meeting of the Emergency Management team." src="https://d3qi0qp55mx5f5.cloudfront.net/safety-security/uploads/page_photos/EM_website_pic_nov_2016_2.jpg" style="width: 570px; height: 380px;"/>
       </p>
       <p>
        The following links identify strategies for public safety for different segments of the University community:
       </p>
       <p>
        <a href="https://safety-security.uchicago.edu/emergency_management/planning_guides_and_resources/what_to_do_students_parents">
         What to Do: Students/Parents
        </a>
        <br/>
        <a href="https://safety-security.uchicago.edu/emergency_management/planning_guides_and_resources/what_to_do_staff_faculty_academic_appointees_postdoctoral_researchers">
         What to Do: Staff/Faculty/Academic Appointees/Postdoctoral Researchers
        </a>
        <br/>
        <a href="https://safety-security.uchicago.edu/emergency_management/planning_guides_and_resources/what_to_do_divisions_departments_units">
         What to Do: Divisions/Departments/Units
        </a>
       </p>
       <p>
        To report an emergency that may threaten the community, contact the University of Chicago Police Department: 123 (on-campus phone), or 773.702.8181 (from an off-campus phone).
       </p>
       <div class="weather">
        <!-- weather-->
        <iframe frameborder="0" height="245" id="forecast_embed" src="https://forecast.io/embed/#lat=41.788659&amp;lon=-87.599654&amp;name=Hyde Park&amp;color=#800000&amp;font=Helvetica" type="text/html" width="100%">
        </iframe>
       </div>
      </article>
